original: Darell, Johan Edvin, komminister, Göteborg, f. 15/5/85 i Bergum, Älvsb. I., av hemm:äg. Johan Jonsson o. Gustaf va Dareiri. G. 17 m. lär. Lydia Johansson. Barn: Greta f. 18, g. m. past:adj. A. Adeil, Söderköp., OM 20, jur. stud., Göran 22, soc :omb :man, Blsa 23, ’Socialas’sis’t. — Stud :ex. i Upps. II, ’teok fil. ex. 12, teok kand., prakt, teol. prov samt prästv. f. Gbgs stift 15. V.^ kommin. i Gällstad 15, kom-min. i Öxabäck 16, i Gbgs Lundby förs. sed. 24. Und. tjgitiden i Öxabäck v. ordf. i kyrko- o. skolråd, ordf. i val-ndn, led. av taxindn m. m., i Lundby v. ordf. i kyrkostämman, led. av Gbgs folkskistyr. 31-43, v. ordf. 36-43, led. av stadsfullm. 39-42, ordf. i Lundby barnkrubba, led. av styr. f. Gbgs präst-gymn. o. Gbgs Stifts Tidn. m. m. Skr.: ett flert. tidn:upps.
translated: Darell, Johan Edvin, vicar, Gothenburg, born May 15th, 1885 in Bergum, Älvsborgs län, to farmer Johan Jonsson and Gustaf va Dareiri. Married at age 17 to teacher Lydia Johansson. Children: Greta (born 1918), married to pastor Adj. A. Adeil in Söderköping, Omar (born 1920), studying law in Gothenburg, Göran (born 1922), social worker, and Blsa (born 1923), a student of social work. Passed exams in Uppsala with a degree in theology and philosophy in 1912, and another degree in practical theology, as well as passing the ordination exam for the Gothenburg diocese in 1915. Became a vicar in Gällstad in 1915, Öxabäck in 1916, and in Gothenburg's Lundby parish from 1924. During his time in Öxabäck, he was the deputy chairman of the church and school council, chairman of the election committee, member of the tax commission, and more. During his tenure in Lundby, he was the deputy chairman of the church council, member of the Gothenburg people's school board from 1931-1943, deputy chairman of the same from 1936-1943, a member of the city council from 1939-1942, chairman of the Lundby daycare center, and a member of the board of Gothenburg’s pastor gymnasium and Gothenburg’s Diocese Journal, among other positions. Published several articles in various newspapers.
